      "content": "I guess. Though, looking at a few of the test cases for the new 'Safe Mode' trajectories, they're pretty rigid. If a kid runs into the street or a car swerves unexpectedly, the Safe Mode kernel won't be able to recalculate a path in real-time; it'll just stay on the pre-set line. It might actually lead to more accidents in edge cases, but the board says the predictability is worth the risk. What do you think about that?",
